			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Bloodforge armor, as well as Blackened armor, offer magical bonuses that are not listed on the item. Runor is that the before useless Identify spell must be cast upon them to reveal lore info and more detail as to their magical property. These bonuses are not stat related, but rather very specific. Such as resistance to a particular species magic, say, goblin shaman spells or such. <BR>
<BR>
At this time I have heard of blackened boots only having an increased atk value vs. orcs while kicking. If someone can confirm this, please let us know. I will be continuing research in the near future after I have aquired more pieces.<BR>
<BR>
Omar<BR>
