		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Well, I found a very upset erudite with the bloodforge boots after he completed the ogre heads quest, and he was asking how much they were worth, dwarf only, after all ye know.  Realizing they were as good as Blackened iron boots, I reminded him that only dwarves could wear them and it might be hard to find a buyer.  I've seen Blackened Boots go for 100pp typically so I offered him an RTS and 30pp, figuring 50pp would be about fair considering the racial/class limitations (dwarf rogues can't wear them).  Beyond looking cool with their deep crimson/bronze color, they don't do me much good- I should probably go with small banded boots, I'm only a cleric and can't kick.  But I think I paid a fair price for them.  I would give them to a dwarf warrior who could use them, but they just look so cool I don't wanna let them go...
			</font>
	
